title: ID_Object_Candlestick_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>The candlestick Richard would always keep in his study. The flames damaged it, but it doesn't look deformed.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>I never really got why he kept it here. This was a well lit room even with the lamps off.</i>) #tone:sigh
Daniel: (<i>Maybe he just wanted to show off his money, but to who? His wife and daughter?</i>)
Daniel: (...) #tone:distressed
Daniel: (<i>Anyways, it can't stay here. Better keep it with me.</i>) #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.Candlestick.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_ImportantStudyDocuments_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: What...! #tone:surprised
Daniel: (<i>How did these documents survive the fire?!</i>) #tone:distressed
Daniel: (<i>There's words covered with different color ink. Judging by the rest of the sentences, the covered words must be names.</i>) #tone:nervous
Daniel: (<i>I must find a way to read them. Maybe aroud the house there's something that can help me.<i>) #tone:serious
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_Whisky_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A bottle of Whisky. Seems nice. And pricey. Must taste good too, the bottle is half gone.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>Richard always liked to drink, I wouldn't be surprised to find a cellar filled with bottles like this one.</i>) #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: (<i>There are no glasses on the counter, however. Wonder who drank it, and for how long it has been sitting here.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>I could ask around.</i>) #tone:neutral
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_ColoredGlasses_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>Glasses with a colored bottom. I'm sure they're Mary's idea.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>They are extremely clean. Were I to use them as a scope, I'd see the room in a completely different color.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>Sounds fun. I wonder if it will ever come in handy.</i>) #tone:happy
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_Salt_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A salt container. Maybe sugar? I cannot be certain by only looking at it.</i>) #tone:question
Daniel: (<i>Just one way to be certain...</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: Mmhg...! #tone:surprised
Daniel: (<i>Salt.</i>) #tone:sigh
===

title: ID_Object_Salt_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>No need to check again. It's salt.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_Salt_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Mary.NotebookCase.Solved
--- 
Daniel: (<i>I have to make it look like Mary's lighter was in the study when the fire started.</i>) #tone:serious
Daniel: (<i>Exposed to the flames, and object like that would rust quickly, so...</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>This could turn out useful.</i>) #tone:serious
===
//FINE


title:ID_Object_OldDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A rag doll? Isn't this the bag Melissa uses for school?</i>) #tone:question
Daniel: (<i>The doll seems quite old, but it well taken care for. How long has Melissa held onto this thing?</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>She even brings it with her at school, risking schoolmates finding it, it must be really important for her.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>I should talk about it with Melissa.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_OldDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A strange doll in a strage place. Better ask about it to the owner.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_OldDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: (<i>One of Melissa's dolls. Probably the oldest one still in her possesion. You can see it by its conditions.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>If she brings it with her at school, it must be really important for her. Could there be more?</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>I should take it with me. I could ask more about it to Melissa, or even Mary.</i>) #tone:neutral
<<SetTag EventFlags.OldDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_RuinedDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>There's a rag doll on the desk. It's surrounded by books and notebooks.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>It stands out. Everything is so new, while it looks rather old.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>Why does Melissa keep it here? Does it help her focus? Or maybe it's a doll capable of doing homework...?</i>) #tone:question
Daniel: (<i>No, it's not the time to joke around. Better ask Melissa.</i>) #tone:serious
===

title: ID_Object_RuinedDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A strange doll in a strage place. Better ask about it to the owner.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_RuinedDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: (<i>One of Melissa's dolls. Looks like one of the older ones. It's on display on the desk, looking at the chair.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>Maybe Melissa pratices with the doll when she has to study? That's a funny image.</i>) #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: (<i>I shouldn't waste time wondering about it. All that matters, is that it seems like an important object.</i>) #tone:serious
Daniel: (<i>I'm sure no one would be offended if I made her take a stroll around the house.</i>) #tone:sarcastic
<<SetTag EventFlags.RuinedDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_PorcelainDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>Up there, there's a porcelain doll. It seems in good condition, desite the dust.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>It looks of great quality, it can't have costed little. Not that money is really a concern for this family.</i>) #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: (<i>It's a bit unsettling up there, in the shadows, looking at you with that stern look...</i>) #tone:distressed
Daniel: (<i>I should ask Melissa why she keeps it there.</i>) #tone:sigh
===

title: ID_Object_PorcelainDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A strange doll in a strage place. Better ask about it to the owner.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_PorcelainDoll_Collected_ENG
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: (<i>One of Melissa's dolls. It seems new, but it's dusty.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>I don't think it's one of her favorites, since she keeps it hidden. But there isn't even a loose thread on it, she still looks after it.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>Does she truly not like it, or is there another reason behind it's location? Mmh...</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>I think it's time to take her down from her dusty refuge and ask Melissa why she has confined it there.</i>) #tone:sarcastic
<<SetTag EventFlags.PorcelainDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title:ID_Object_NewPorcelainDoll_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A porcellain doll under Melissa's bed? How did it end up here?</i>) #tone:surprised
Daniel: (<i>It's brand new, not dirty nor dusty. It cannot have been here for long.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>Now this is really weird. And suspicious. Did she try to hide it? Why?</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>Well, there is only one way to discover it. Better talk about it with Melissa.</i>) #tone:serious
===

title: ID_Object_NewPorcelainDoll_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A strange doll in a strage place. Better ask about it to the owner.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_NewPorcelainDoll_Collected_ITA
tag: EventFlags.Melissa.Dialogues.AboutYou.Completed
---
Daniel: (<i>One of Melissa's dolls, hidden under the bed... for some reason.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>It must be the newest one she owns. I think I've seen the same doll in the shops last month.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>She seems to care for her dolls, so this can't be it's usual spot. And since there's nothing out of place, it cannot have ended up here as a mistake.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>If she hid it it must be important, so it must be important. Better Tale it with me.</i>) #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.NewPorcelainDoll.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_MelissaSecretDiary_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A secret diary hidden behind a locket. Even spoiled girly can be crafty when needed.</i>) #tone:thinking
Daniel: (<i>If Melissa went to such lenght to hide her diary, it must hold some really important secrets.</i>) #tone:serious
Daniel: (<i>It's a bit uncomfortable reading the intimate thoughts of a sixteen years old, but after all this effort to find the diary, it would be dumb not to read it.</i>) #tone:distressed
Daniel: (<i>Plus, there could be written something regarding Richard. I could find a motive, or maybe something even more important...</i>) #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.MelissaSecretDiary.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_BedroomAshtray_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>A used ashtray, sat on the nightstand. Mary musn't have had the time to clean it up, seeing all that happened.</i>) #tone:neutral
Daniel: (<i>Is this Richard's or Mary's nightstand? They look the same so I can't really tell them apart.</i>) #tone:question
Daniel: (<i>Anyways, smoking in the bedroom doesn't seem like a great idea. I hope they at least opened the window.</i>) #tone:sigh
Daniel: (<i>I can always take it and ask around about its owner.</i>) #tone:neutral
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_WeddingSheets_Collected_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>These papers... They are the prenup between Richard and Mary. Why would they keep something so important here?</i>) #tone:surprised
Daniel: (<i>Well, obviously Richard had his wife sign a contract before sharing his wealth.</i>) #tone:sarcastic
Daniel: (<i>I don't think these papers could benefit him now.</i>) #tone:grim
Daniel: (<i>Still, I'm sure the hold important information. I should take a look.</i>) #tone:serious
<<SetTag EventFlags.WeddingSheets.PickedUp true>>
===
//FINE


title: ID_Object_MaryLighter_Seen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>What's this? A tin box? I can't really make it out.</i>) #tone:question
Daniel: (<i>It looks like it has some colorful decoration. Maybe it fell here?</i>) #tone:question
Daniel: (<i>I chould try talking about it with Mary, she should know about it.</i>) #tone:neutral
===

title: ID_Object_MaryLighter_AlreadySeen_ENG
---
Daniel: (<i>The one person that knows what that is, is Mary.</i>) #tone:neutral
